@c --------------------------------------------------------
@subsection Key Binding

``Power users'' of Coot might like to write their own functions and bind
that function to a keyboard key.  How do they do that?

By using the add-key-binding function:

@code{(add-key-binding @emph{function-name key function})}

where @code{@emph{key}} is a quoted string (note that upper case and
lower case keys are distinguished - activate get upper case key binding
you need to chord the shift key @footnote{funny that}).

for example:

